text: The 2019 Rutland County Council election took place on 2 May 2019 to elect members of Rutland County Council in England. This was on the same day as other local elections. New boundaries were used in this election and the number of councillors increased from 26 to 27. == Results summary == === Barleythorpe === === Braunston & Martinsthorpe === === Cottesmore === === Exton === === Greetham === === Ketton === === Langham === === Lyddington === === Normanton === === Oakham North East === === Oakham North West === === Oakham South === === Ryhall & Casterton === === Uppingham === === Whissendine === == References == == External links == * Category:2019 English local elections Category:May 2019 events in the United Kingdom 2019
